                  </persName>
            . I am a widow: I went out the 19th of July about one at night; I locked my door and went to Water-lane; while I was there, Mrs. Newey told me somebody had been in, my house; when she came up she brought the prisoner at the bar with her; I went home and found my door broke open; I missed some of the things mentioned in the indictment. The prisoner had two pillows, a pair of salts and the glass in her apron; the other things were scattered about in my house but were not taken away. The prisoner at that time was very much in liquor.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17730908-55-person597">
                  Mary
                   Newey
               <interp inst="t17730908-55-person597" type="surname" value="Newey"></interp>
